  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Cloud Engineer",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a motivated Cloud DevOps Engineer with a strong interest in automation to join our team. The ideal candidate will have experience building and managing AWS infrastructure and be proficient in Infrastructure as Code (IaC) to enhance security, availability, and operational efficiency.</p><h3><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li>Design, build, and manage AWS infrastructure using IaC tools such as GitLab, Terraform, Sentinel, and Ansible</li><li>Enhance the efficiency and reliability of Control Tower/Landing Zone pipelines, workflows, Lambda functions, and CloudFormation stacks/stacksets</li><li>Automate routine operations using AWS tools (Lambda, Step Functions, Systems Manager)</li><li>Collaborate with application engineers to align automation tasks with business needs</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve AWS infrastructure issues</li><li>Implement security best practices for AWS environments</li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Minimum 3 years of hands-on experience with <strong>RHEL</strong></li><li>Experience in <strong>Ansible</strong> and strong shell scripting skills preferred</li><li>Knowledge of CI/CD and IaC tools such as GitLab, Terraform, and CloudFormation</li><li>Proficiency with AWS automation tools (Lambda, Step Functions, Systems Manager)</li><li>Familiarity with Python, Bash, or PowerShell</li><li>Strong understanding of AWS security best practices</li><li>Cloud certifications (AWS/Azure/GCP) are a plus</li><li>Strong communication and teamwork skills</li></ul><p>(EA Reg No: 20C0312)</p><p>Please email a copy of your detailed resume to <strong>qianyu@talentsis.com.sg</strong> for immediate processing.</p><p>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
